cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper deals with black-box attacks on machine learning classifiers, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on minimizing the number of queries to the model, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.CR (cryptography and security).
